<p>Average salary information is sourced from the <a class="uline" href="https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/labour/earnings-and-working-conditions/employee-earnings-and-hours-australia/latest-release" target="_blank">Australian Bureau of Statistics</a>&nbsp;<i class="icon-tiny fa fa-external-link"></i> (ABS) through the <b>Employee Earnings and Hours (EEH) survey</b>. The EEH survey is conducted every <b>two years</b> and provides detailed insights into employee earnings across Australia.</p>
<p>Due to Covid-19, the next survey is expected to be conducted in 2021 and released in early 2022.</p><p>The data below contains estimates from the 2018 Survey of Employee Earnings and Hours which was conducted in May 2018.</p>
